## Cross-Surface Linking Rules

Cross-surface navigation must behave intentionally.

### Allowed conceptual flows
- Public -> Sign In / Register
- Public -> Client Portal (after auth)
- Public -> Admin Portal (staff auth)
- Public -> Applications explanation pages
- Client Portal -> Application Layer module launch experience
- Admin Portal -> internal application, content, or oversight views

### Disallowed conceptual flows
- Public -> raw repository URLs
- Client Portal -> raw infrastructure, direct vendor admin panels, or unmanaged tools
- Admin Portal -> public-facing route semantics for sensitive operations
- Application Layer -> bypass of portal or shell meaning

### Required rule
Every cross-surface transition must later be governable by:
- identity
- entitlement
- customer/account state
- launch model
- role/permission rules

The skeleton must visually allow this, not block it.

