## Route-State Requirements

Every route in the final sitemap must be designed to support route-level state handling later.

### Required universal states
- loading
- empty
- success
- warning
- error
- access-restricted

### Additional route states by surface

#### Public
- authenticated redirect
- gated content prompt
- conversion success
- form error

#### Client
- onboarding required
- payment hold
- compliance hold
- no entitlement
- partial access

#### Admin
- insufficient permission
- approval required
- queue empty
- sync/integration issue

#### Application layer
- available
- restricted
- onboarding required
- pending activation
- launch unavailable

The route map must be built with these states in mind, even if the skeleton uses mock data.

